President Barack Obama has established a new Presidential Commission for the Study of Bioethical Issues. The purpose of the commission is to advise the President on bioethical issues that may arise from advances in biomedicine and related areas of science and technology. Amy Gutmann has been appointed as the Chair of the commission, and James W. Wagner as the Vice Chair. The commission will work towards identifying and promoting policies and practices that ensure ethical conduct in scientific research, healthcare delivery, and technological innovation. The President has also appointed other individuals to the commission, including experts in political science, philosophy, ethics, and public policy.